QUESTION:
The Nautilus development team shared with the DevOps team requirements for new application development, setting up a Git repository for that project. 
Create a Git repository on Storage server in Stratos DC as per details given below:

Install git package using yum on Storage server.

After that create/init a git repository /opt/official.git (use the exact name as asked and make sure not to create a bare repository).


SOLUTION:
Change to storage server.
$ ssh natash@ststor01

Change to the opt directory
# cd /opt/

Create or init a git repo
# git init official.git
Initialized empty Git repository in /opt/official.git/.git/




